## ğŸ¯ Overview
Project Daedalus transforms CNC and programming education into a **tactile and inclusive experience**.  
It allows students who are blind or visually impaired to build CNC programs using **Braille blocks** arranged on a **magnetic board**, simulating the structure of real G-code and logic.

## ğŸ§© Quick Start
1. Visit the [Quick Start Guide](quickstart.md)  
2. Download and print the 3D pieces from the [`/stl`](../../stl/) folder  
3. Assemble the **magnetic board and Braille blocks** (see [Mechanical Assembly](section-06_mechanical-assembly.md))  
4. Try the examples in [`/examples`](../../examples/) for your first lesson  

